@NODE Archiv "CxBar/What should be in the archive?"

The following files should be in the archiv:
@{LINDENT 3}
@{b}tools/VPI@{ub}                      --> a viewer for Product-Info files

@{b}env/mui/CXBAR.prefs@{ub}            --> mui prefs file for CxBar
@{b}env/mui/CXBAR.cfg@{ub}              --> my config file for CxBar
  I highly suggest you to copy this to your @{b}ENV:MUI/@{ub},
  cause this is the way I wanted @{b}CxBar@{ub} to look like!

@{b}catalogs/deutsch/CxBar.catalog@{ub} --> german catalog
@{b}catalogs/deutsch/CxBar_D.ct@{ub}    --> german catalog-translation
@{b}catalogs/CxBar_blank.ct@{ub}        --> blank catalog-translation

@{b}help/deutsch/CxBar.guide@{ub}       --> german documentation, AmigaGuide-Format
@{b}help/deutsch/AFD-COPYRIGHT.de@{ub}  --> german COPYRIGHT-Note
@{b}help/english/CxBar.guide@{ub}       --> english documentation, AmigaGuide-Format
@{b}help/english/AFD-COPYRIGHT@{ub}     --> english COPYRIGHT-Note

@{b}rexx/*@{ub}                         --> some example rexx-scripts

@{b}Registration.txt@{ub}               --> english registration formular
@{b}Registrierung.txt@{ub}              --> german registration formular
@{b}Product-Info@{ub}                   --> product info
@{b}Preview.gif@{ub}                    --> preview picture of @{b}CxBar@{ub}

@{b}CxBar.readme@{ub}                   --> short english doc, ASCII
@{b}CxBar.liesmich@{ub}                 --> short german doc, ASCII
@{b}CxBar@{ub}                          --> the program
@{b}CxBar.info@{ub}                     --> icon for the program
@ENDNODE

@NODE WhatItIs "CxBar/What is this program for?"
@{LINDENT 3}
This  program  controls  all  commodities  in  your  system.  It is an
alternative for the normal Exchange and uses the @{" MagicUserInterface " link MUI}
by Stefan Stuntz.

The difference between C='s (or AT's) Exchange and @{b}CxBar@{ub} is that @{b}CxBar@{ub}
displays  the  commodities  as  buttons  (cycles) in a horizontical or
vertical (switchable!), one-line (bar) or one-row virtual group.
Every  button  has  a  help-bubble  which  shows  the  title  and  the
description  of the commodity and informs you if it has a window which
can be shown and hidden ("GUI:  YES" or "GUI:  NO").

Also you  can  turn  on  a @{"size-gadget" link Menus} to size the window and a drag-
gadget to change the window's position.
The size-gadget appears on the right or bottom and the @{"drag-gadget" link Menus} on
the left or top.
You  can  also have the window the normal/intuition windowborder incl.
all @{"bordergadgets" link Menus}.

@{b}CxBar@{ub}  has  also some  @{"arexx commands" link ARexx}  to control the commodities via
arexx and it is localizied!
It has also a rexx menu  where you can start  rexx-scripts direct from
@{b}CxBar@{ub}!

The help-bubble of @{b}CxBar@{ub} looks like this:
       ____________________________________
      /                                    \\
     | CxBar 37.23 (30.05.97) by T. Igracki |
     | A new Exchange clone.                |
     |                                      |
     |                GUI: YES              |
      \\___  _______________________________/
          \\ \\
           \\ \\
            \\/

If  you click on a button (left mouse) a popupmenu will be shown where
you can select one of the following commands/actions:

    ----------
   |  Remove  |  -> remove/kill the commodity (w/o requester!)
   |  Disable |  -> deactivate the commodity
   |  Enable  |  -> activate the commodity
   |   Hide   |  -> hide the commodity/window
   |   Show   |  -> show/popup the commodity/window
   | Exchange |  -> the name of the commodity, no function
    ----------

If the menu entry @{"Options/Toggle Activity?" link Menus} is selected, then the popupmenu
looks like this:

    ----------
   |  Remove  | 
   |  Toggle  | -> toggle the activity
   |   Hide   |
   |   Show   |
   | Exchange |
    ----------

If a commodity didn't has a window/GUI to popup/hide the entries @{b}Hide@{ub}
and @{b}Show@{ub} won't be there!

If a commodity is inactive the name will be shown in italic style.


Hint:
  If  you  have a three-button-mouse, you can use the middle button to
  scroll the buttons to the left or right!
  If not set @{"Option/Scrollbar?" link Menus}.

@ENDNODE

@NODE HowToStart "CxBar/How to start"
@{LINDENT 3}
@{b}Start from a shell:@{ub}
   
   [Run] [<>NIL:] @{b}CxBar@{ub}

@{b}Start from Workbench:@{ub}

   Just  double-click the icon.


Its  the best, if you copy @{b}CxBar@{ub} to the WBStartup-Dir or start
it in User-Startup.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Menus "CxBar/Description of the menus"

@{b}Project@{ub}
   About...         ? - Some infos about CxBar
   About MUI...       - Some infos about MUI
   ------------------
   Hide             H - Hide CxBar's window.
   ------------------
   Quit             Q - Quit CxBar immediately.

@{b}Window@{ub}
   Position        >> - A submenu to quickly  set the position of the
                        window  to  the  top   (under  the  titlebar),
                        bottom, left or right of the screen.
   ------------------
   Snapshot           - Snapshot the windows position and size
                        (just like the item in the windows popup-menu)
   UnSnapshot         - UnSnapshot the windows position and size
                        (just like the item in the windows popup-menu)

@{b}Rexx@{ub}                  - It only appears if the directory @{b}Rexx:CxBar/@{ub} isn't empty!
   Update             - Update the rexx menu. CxBar will re-read the directory Rexx:CxBar.
   ------------------   This is neccessary, because the filesystem FFS doesn't
                        sent a notifysignal if you delete a file in directory!
                        Newly created files are recognized and the menu will
                        be updated automatically!
   ...                - One menuitem per file in @{b}Rexx:CxBar/@{ub}.
                        You can now start the script by selecting this item.

@{b}Options@{ub}
   Scrollbar?       1 - Should there be a scrollbar?
                        Its  for  scrolling  the  virtualgroup  if you
                        don't have a 3-button-mouse else you can use
                        the middle button for scrolling!
   Vertical?        2 - Vertical or horizontal buttons?
   Iconify gadget?  3 - Should there be an iconify gadget?
                        Same as Project/Hide.
                        Presented  by a button with an "I" at the left
                        or top.
                        The hotkey is "numpad *".
   Drag gadget?     4 - Should there be a drag gadget to drag the window?
                        Presented by a blank button on the left or top
                        to set the position of the window.
   Size gadget?     5 - Should there be a size gadget to size the window?
                        Presented  by  a  blank button on the right or
                        bottom to change the size of the window.
   Window gadgets?  6 - Windowborders incl. all bordergadgets?
   Toggle Activity? 7 - One or two commands for changing the activity?
   ------------------
   MUI...           0 - Set MUI-specific settings
   ------------------
   Use                - Use settings
   Save               - Save settings

@ENDNODE

@NODE ARexx "CxBar/Description of the arexx commands"

Here  the output of MUI's ARexxCommand HELP to show you which commands
@{b}CxBar@{ub} understands:
@{LINDENT 3}
Standard-Commands:

Command      Template
-------      --------
quit         FORCE/S
hide         
deactivate   
show         
activate     
info         ITEM/A
help         FILE/A


Commands for application "Exchange":

Command      Template
-------      --------
CX           NAME/A,SHOW/S,HIDE/S,ON=ENABLE/S,OFF=DISABLE/S,KILL=REMOVE/S
CxList       VERBOSE/S
CxGet        NAME,TITLE/S,DESCR/S,ENTRIES/S

@{LINDENT 0}
For the standard commands please see the mui docs.


Commands for application "Exchange":

CX NAME/A,SHOW/S,HIDE/S,ON=ENABLE/S,OFF=DISABLE/S,KILL=REMOVE/S
---------------------------------------------------------------
@{LINDENT 3}
The command @{b}CX@{ub} send the commodity specified by the parameter @{b}NAME@{ub} one
of the following commands:

  SHOW           : pop up the window (if it has one)
  HIDE           : hide the window
  ON or ENABLE   : enable the commodity
  OFF or DISABLE : disable the commodity
  KILL or REMOVE : remove the commodity

If more then on of these parameters are given, then only the first (in
the above order) will be used!

NAME can contain AmigaDOS-Pattern, and all matching names will receive
the  command!   The name is compared with no case and if it has spaces
you have to quote the name or use wildcards!

If  an  error  occured,  maybe you forgot the NAME or the NAME doesn't
exists, the ARexx variable RC will contain a number unlike 0.
If  the  NAME doesn't exists, the ARexx variable RESULT will contain a
appropriate message.

Examples:

  CX exchange show    --> popup @{b}CxBar@{ub}s window
  CX #? show          --> popup the window of all commodities!
  CX #? hide          --> hide the window of all commodities!
  CX #? off           --> disable all commodities!
  CX exch#? show kill --> only popup the window of all
                          commodities matching this pattern.
                          They don't get killed, cause SHOW will
                          be checked first!
@{LINDENT 0}
CxList VERBOSE/S
----------------
@{LINDENT 3}
The command @{b}CxList@{ub} is used to  get a list of all currently running
commodities.
If the parameter @{b}VERBOSE@{ub} is specified,  then the list will contain
more infos, not only the names. The names will be also quoted.

The  ARexx  variable  RESULT  (only  if  you  called "OPTIONS RESULTS"
before!) will contain the result of the command.

Examples:

  Here is the output of @{b}CxList@{ub} on my system:

  Directory Opus 5
  EasyCED
  Exchange
  Executive
  Magic Menu
  MCP
  ModePro
  OMouse
  OMouse.gui
  OOL
  Scout
  ScreenClock
  YACE

  And this is the output of @{b}CxList VERBOSE@{ub}:

  "Directory Opus 5" GUI Active
  "EasyCED" NoGUI Active
  "Exchange" GUI Active
  "Executive" NoGUI Active
  "Magic Menu" GUI Active
  "MCP" GUI Active
  "ModePro" GUI Active
  "OMouse" GUI Active
  "OMouse.gui" GUI Active
  "OOL" GUI Active
  "Scout" GUI Active
  "ScreenClock" GUI Active
  "YACE" GUI Active

@{LINDENT 0}
CxGet NAME,TITLE/S,DESCR/S,ENTRIES/S
------------------------------------
@{LINDENT 3}
The command @{b}CxGet@{ub} returns the TITLE or DESCRiption from one specified
commodity or the number of ENTRIES of all commodities in your system.

NAME can contain AmigaDOS-Pattern, and all matching names will receive
the  command!   The name is compared with no case and if it has spaces
you have to quote the name or use wildcards!
This  option  has  to  be  specified  if you use the option TITLE/S or
DESCR/S!

The  ARexx  variable  RESULT  (only  if  you  called "OPTIONS RESULTS"
before!) will contain the result of the command.

Examples:

  @{b}CxGet Exchange TITLE@{ub}
  --> CxBar 37.20 (26.04.97) by T. Igracki
  
  @{b}CxGet "exc*" TITLE@{ub}
  --> CxBar 37.20 (26.04.97) by T. Igracki

  @{b}CxGet "exc*" DESCR@{ub}
  --> A new Exchange clone.
  
  @{b}CxGet "*opus*" TITLE@{ub}
  --> ©1996 Jonathan Potter & GPSoftware
  
  @{b}CxGet ENTRIES@{ub}
  --> 13

@ENDNODE

@NODE Register "CxBar/Registering"
@{LINDENT 3}
You only have to fill out the @{"register formular" link Registration.txt} and send it to me.
@{"Via eMail or snail mail" link Me}.
You     can     also     register     direct     on     my    homepage
@{b}http://home.pages.de/~lokai/amiga/RegisterE.html@{ub}!

The share for @{b}CxBar@{ub} is $10, 10DM or the appropriate amount of your
countries money.
@{"You can transfer it to my bank-account or send it in cash." link Me}

In  the  @{b}unregistered@{ub}  version  there appears a requester from time to
time which should remind you to pay the share!

If  you  register  @{b}CxBar@{ub},  you'll  get  a keyfile, which turns off the
reminder-requesters.

@ENDNODE

